The Guardian’s picture editors bring you a selection of photo highlights from around the world, including preparations for Mainz carnival and newly discovered miniature night frogs Tuesday 21 February 2017 13.20 GMT Zawiya, Libya Red Crescent volunteers gather scores of bodies, presumed to be African migrants, after they washed ashore on the country’s Mediterranean coast Photograph: Libyan Red Crescent/EPA Hebron, West Bank The parents of Palestinian Abdul Fatah al-Sharif, who was shot dead by Israeli military medic Elor Azaria as he lay incapacitated, watch the delivery of the verdict of his trial Photograph: Hazem Bader/AFP/Getty Melbourne, Australia A blaze rages after a charter plane crashed into a retail outlet, killing a pilot and four US tourists Photograph: Xinhua/Barcroft Snow settles on a security guard’s uniform as he stands outside an office building Photograph: Mark Schiefelbein/AP London, England Charles Keidan and Rebecca Steinfeld address the media outside the Royal Courts of Justice after they lost their fight to enter a civil partnership Photograph: Jack Taylor/Getty Images A giant Iron Man statue stands next to a replica Sphinx in Chuzhou Photograph: Rex/Shutterstock Five cheetah cubs at the Safaripark Beekse Bergen Photograph: Remko de Waal/EPA A cruise ship leaves the harbour Photograph: Adalberto Roque/AFP/Getty Mainz, Germany A carnival float named Rule Britannia depicts a figure in a lifeboat gesturing to a departing European ship Photograph: Ronald Wittek/EPA Kerala, India A 13.6mm ‘ night frog. Scientists have discovered four species of miniature night frogs small enough to sit on a fingernail Photograph: SD Biju/AFP/Getty
